          How many working class Aussie boys grow up to be showgirls? Based 
          on the extraordinary life of the iconic Les Girls headliner and 
          Australian transgender pioneer, Jessica Marais (Magic City, Packed

          a transsexual was, Carlotta was pushing the boundaries of gender 
          and sexuality. She was an ambassador for rebellion, freedom, and 
          self-expression: a living, breathing symbol of emerging 60s liberalism.

          seventies. Against the threat of criminal prosecution as well as 
          social rejection, Carlotta emerges as the all conquering drag queen 
          and performer. Spanning forty years, Carlotta is an uplifting
